{"lemma":"رُكْبَةُ","slug":"رُكْبَةُ","root":"ر.ك.ب","root_slug":"ر-ك-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ك-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n16451","n16459","n16460","n16461","n16462"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%8F%D9%83%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"knee"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of رَاكِب (rākib)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Perhaps from Proto-Semitic *rukba- (“knee”), metathetic form of Proto-Semitic *birk- (“knee”)."},"ipa":["/ruk.ba/","/ra.ka.ba/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n16451","headword_ar":"رَكِبَهُ","root":"rkb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, * A, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakiba Ealayohi","text_ar":"رَكِبَ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukuwbN","text_ar":"رُكُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marokabN","text_ar":"مَرْكَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A, K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Artkbhu","text_ar":"ارتكبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaAhu","text_ar":"عَلَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaA Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَلَا عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[explained by what follows]. (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakibotu Ald~aAb~apa","text_ar":"رَكِبْتُ الدَّابَّةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alfarasa","text_ar":"الفَرَسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakibotu EalayohaA","text_ar":"رَكِبْتُ عَلَيْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", [or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukuwbN","text_ar":"رُكُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marokabN","text_ar":"مَرْكَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as above, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I rode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rode upon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I mounted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mounted upon, the beast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the horse"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA. [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAkibN","text_ar":"رَاكِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakibotu Als~afiynapa","text_ar":"رَكِبْتُ السَّفِينَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Als~afiynapi","text_ar":"فِى السَّفِينَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(agreeably with the Kur xi. 43 and xviii. 70 and xxix. 65),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I embarked in the ship; went on board the ship."},{"kind":"text","text":"] And one says, of anything,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakibahu","text_ar":"رَكِبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Artkbh","text_ar":"ارتكبه","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"] as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaAhu","text_ar":"عَلَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, upon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"over, it; got upon it; came,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arose, upon it; overlay it; was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, superincumbent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"supernatant, upon it; overspread it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; namely, another thing. (TA.) [In like manner,] one says also, of anything,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukiba","text_ar":"رُكِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aurotukiba","text_ar":"اُرْتُكِبَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuliYa","text_ar":"عُلِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e., when said of a horse or the like,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was ridden,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ridden upon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was mounted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mounted upon:"},{"kind":"text","text":"whence other significations in other cases, indicated above]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakiba baEoDuhu baEoDFA","text_ar":"رَكِبَ بَعْضُهُ بَعْضًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"trAkb","text_ar":"تراكب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It lay one part upon another; it was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, heaped,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piled, up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"together, one part upon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"overlying, another:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] said of fat [as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, disposed in layers, one above another:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAkibapN","text_ar":"رَاكِبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) [And hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakiba Aln~aAsu","text_ar":"رَكِبَ النَّاسُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEoDuhumo baEoDFA","text_ar":"بَعْضُهُمْ بَعْضًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people bore,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pressed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crowded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as though mounting,"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one upon another;"},{"kind":"text","text":"a phrase well known, and of frequent occurrence: or meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the people followed one another closely;"},{"kind":"text","text":"from what next follows.] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakibahu","text_ar":"رَكِبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also means [(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He came upon him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"overtook him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he followed closely,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"immediately, after him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakibotu A^avarahu","text_ar":"رَكِبْتُ اَثَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tariyqahu","text_ar":"طَرِيقَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I followed close after him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.) ―         -b4-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakiba AlT~ariyqa","text_ar":"رَكِبَ الطَّرِيقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~amola","text_ar":"الرَّمْلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmafaAzapa","text_ar":"المَفَازَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went upon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trod,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"travelled, the road,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the sand"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sands, and the desert:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakiba AlbaHora","text_ar":"رَكِبَ البَحْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He embarked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"voyaged, upon the sea."},{"kind":"text","text":"Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakiba All~ayola","text_ar":"رَكِبَ اللَّيْلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alhawola","text_ar":"الهَوْلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He ventured upon, encountered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"braved, the night,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that which was terrible"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fearful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and the like thereof. (TA.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakiba A^amorFA","text_ar":"رَكِبَ اَمْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Artkbhu","text_ar":"ارتكبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He ventured upon, embarked in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"undertook, an affair:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he surmounted it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mastered it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the former meaning is well known: the latter is indicated by an explanation of the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rak~aAbN","text_ar":"رَكَّابٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liloA^umuwri","text_ar":"لِلْاُمُورِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which see below.] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakiba *anobFA","text_ar":"رَكِبَ ذَنْبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Artkbhu","text_ar":"ارتكبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, MA, K) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He committed a sin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crime,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, MA, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakiba","text_ar":"رَكِبَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN fulaAnFA biA^amorK","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ فُلَانًا بِاَمْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one did to such a one a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakibahu bimakoruwhK","text_ar":"رَكِبَهُ بِمَكْرُوهٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Artkbhu","text_ar":"ارتكبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He did to him an evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abominable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"odious, deed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakibotu Ald~ayona","text_ar":"رَكِبْتُ الدَّيْنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Artkbthu","text_ar":"ارتكبتهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I became much in debt:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakibaniY Ald~ayonu","text_ar":"رَكِبَنِى الدَّيْنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArtkbnY","text_ar":"ارتكبنى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Debt burdened me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakiba","text_ar":"رَكِبَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^osahu","text_ar":"رَاْسَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went at random, heedlessly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a headlong manner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maDaY EalaY wajohihi","text_ar":"مَضَى عَلَى وَجْهِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", A, Msb,) [i. e.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without consideration,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without any certain aim,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"object,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not obeying a guide to the right course."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yurokabu raA^osahu laA","text_ar":"يُرْكَبُ رَاْسَهُ لَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yadoriY A^ayona yatawaj~ahu","text_ar":"يَدْرِى اَيْنَ يَتَوَجَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He goes at random,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not knowing whither to direct himself"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kmh","text_ar":"كمه"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakobapN","text_ar":"رَكْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". In like manner also, you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakiba raA^oyahu","text_ar":"رَكِبَ رَاْيَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aisotahaj~a","text_ar":"اِسْتَهَجَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He followed his own opinion."},{"kind":"text","text":"And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakiba hawaAhu","text_ar":"رَكِبَ هَوَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jmH","text_ar":"جمح"},{"kind":"text","text":") (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He followed his own natural desire, without consideration, and not obeying a guide to the right course of conduct."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakibotu dub~atahu","text_ar":"رَكِبْتُ دُبَّتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dub~ahu","text_ar":"دُبَّهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I kept to his state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition, and his way, mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of acting"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"did as he did."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"db","text_ar":"دب"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakibatohu AlHum~aY","text_ar":"رَكِبَتْهُ الحُمَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The fever continued upon him"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is a phrase similar to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^agobaTatohu AlHum~aY","text_ar":"اَغْبَطَتْهُ الحُمَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimotaTatohu","text_ar":"اِمْتَطَتْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AirotaHalatohu","text_ar":"اِرْتَحَلَتْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gbT","text_ar":"غبط"},{"kind":"text","text":")       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakabahu","text_ar":"رَكَبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakobN","text_ar":"رَكْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) [from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukobapN","text_ar":"رُكْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He struck,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smote, his knee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K:) or it signifies, (K,) or signifies also, (S, A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he struck him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smote him, with his knee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he took him by his hair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the hair of each side of his head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and struck his forehead with his knee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) Hence, in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakabotu","text_ar":"رَكَبْتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anofahu birukobatiY","text_ar":"اَنْفَهُ بِرُكْبَتِى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I struck his nose with my knee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And in another trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amaA taEorifu AlA^azoda warakobahaA","text_ar":"اَمَا تَعْرِفُ الاَزْدَ وَرَكْبَهَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ait~aqi AlA^azoda laA yaA^oxu*uwka fayarokubuwka","text_ar":"اِتَّقِ الاَزْدَ لَا يَاْخُذُوكَ فَيَرْكُبُوكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Knowest thou not El-Azd,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the tribe so called,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and their striking with the knee? Beware thou of El-Azd, lest they take thee, and strike thee with their knees"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: for this practice was notorious among El-Azd; in the dial. of whom,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u kayosaAna","text_ar":"اُمُّ كَيْسَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"was a metonymical appellation of the knee. (TA.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukiba","text_ar":"رُكِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuniYa","text_ar":"عُنِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [pass. in form, but neut. in signification,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had a complaint of his knee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakiba","text_ar":"رَكِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakabN","text_ar":"رَكَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was large in the knee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["A","K","S","TA","Msb","Mgh","MA"]},{"entry_id":"n16459","headword_ar":"رَكْبَةٌ","root":"rkb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A single ride,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"act of riding:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakabaAtN","text_ar":"رَكَبَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAth, L.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,] one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa","text_ar":"هُوَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yamo$iY Alr~akobapa","text_ar":"يَمْشِى الرَّكْبَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  [i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yarokabu raA^osahu","text_ar":"يَرْكَبُ رَاْسَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He goes at random, heedlessly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a headlong manner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c., (see 1,)] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humo yamo$uwna Alr~akabaAti","text_ar":"هُمْ يَمْشُونَ الرَّكَبَاتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They go at random,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (A. [The meaning is there indicated by the context, and is shown by what here follows.]) Respecting the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tmo$uwna Alr~akabaAti","text_ar":"تمْشُونَ الرَّكَبَاتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", occurring in a trad., meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarokabuwna ruw^uwsakumo","text_ar":"تَرْكَبُونَ رُوُوسَكُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ye go at random,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in that which is false, wrong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vain, and in factions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seditions,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, following one another without consideration,"},{"kind":"text","text":"IAth says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakobapN","text_ar":"رَكْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[properly] signifies as explained above in the first sentence of this paragraph, and that the pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlrkbAt","text_ar":"الركبات"},{"kind":"text","text":"is here governed in the accus. case by a verb understood, and [with that verb] is a denotative of state relating to the agent in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tm$wn","text_ar":"تمشون"},{"kind":"text","text":": it supplies the place of that verb, which it does not require to be expressed; and the implied meaning is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamo$uwna tarokabuwna","text_ar":"تَمْشُونَ تَرْكَبُونَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~akabaAti","text_ar":"الرَّكَبَاتِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n16460","headword_ar":"رُكْبَةٌ","root":"rkb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a word of well-known meaning, (S, Msb,) [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e., in a man,] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"joint between the lower parts of the thigh and the upper parts of the shank:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K:) or [in a quadruped,] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"joint between the metacarpus and the radius"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawoSilu AlwaZiyfi waAl*~iraAEi","text_ar":"مَوْصِلُ الوَظِيفِ وَالذِّرَاعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"): this is the right explanation: in the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawoDiE","text_ar":"مَوْضِع"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawoSil","text_ar":"مَوْصِل"},{"kind":"text","text":": [this explanation is evidently given accord. to the terms employed in the anatomy of quadrupeds as compared to human beings: in that which next follows, there is certainly an omission, which I have endeavoured to supply:] or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukobataAni","text_ar":"رُكْبَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the fore legs of the camel are the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two joints that"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"project forwards, in like manner as do, in the hind legs, those that"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"are next the belly"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the stifle-joints"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when he lies down upon his breast with folded legs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the two joints that project behind [in the hind legs, namely, the hocks,] are called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuroquwbaAni","text_ar":"عُرْقُوبَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": in every quadruped, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rkbtAn","text_ar":"ركبتان"},{"kind":"text","text":"are in the fore legs, and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ErqwbAn","text_ar":"عرقوبان"},{"kind":"text","text":"are in the hind legs: and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Erqwb","text_ar":"عرقوب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is what is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawoSilu AlwaZiyfi","text_ar":"مَوْصِلُ الوَظِيفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. the upper joint of the metatarsus]: (TA:) or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rkbp","text_ar":"ركبة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mirofaq","text_ar":"مِرْفَق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which in a man is the elbow, but here seems to mean the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lower joint"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iraAE","text_ar":"ذِرَاع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"radius"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of anything [i. e. of any beast]: (K:) [from its being said in the S and Msb that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukobap","text_ar":"رُكْبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is “ well known, ” I conclude that there is no real discrepancy in the foregoing explanations: it is perhaps needless to add that the term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukobap","text_ar":"رُكْبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is now universally applied to the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knee"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man and to what we commonly call the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knee"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a horse and the like:] the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukabN","text_ar":"رُكَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) i. e. the pl. of mult., and the pl. of pauc. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukobaAtN","text_ar":"رُكْبَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukabaAtN","text_ar":"رُكَبَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukubaAtN","text_ar":"رُكُبَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) Lh mentions the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEiyrN musotawoqiHu Alr~ukabi","text_ar":"بَعِيرٌ مُسْتَوْقِحُ الرُّكَبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A hardkneed camel"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as though the term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rukobapN","text_ar":"رُكْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"were applied to each part, and the pl. used accord. to this application. (TA.) ―         -b2-  One says [of an agitating affair or event],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amorN A@SoTak~ato fiyhi Alr~ukabu waHak~ato","text_ar":"اَمْرٌ ا@صْطَكَّتْ فِيهِ الرُّكَبُ وَحَكَّتْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyhi Alr~ukobapu Alr~ukabapa","text_ar":"فِيهِ الرُّكْبَةُ الرُّكَبَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"event, in which the knees knocked together, and in which the knee rubbed the knee"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b3-  And of one who has the mark of prostration in prayer on his forehead, between his eyes, (L,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayona Eayonayohi mivolu rukobapi AlEanozi","text_ar":"بَيْنَ عَيْنَيْهِ مِثْلُ رُكْبَةِ العَنْزِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Between his eyes is the like of the knee of the she-goat"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, * L.) And of any two things that are alike, or correspondent,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humaA karukobataY AlEanozi","text_ar":"هُمَا كَرُكْبَتَى العَنْزِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They are like the two knees of the she-goat"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; because her two knees fall together upon the ground when she lies down. (L.) ―         -b4-  And it is said in a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~u","text_ar":"شَرُّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAsi mano miloHuhu EalaY rukEbatihi","text_ar":"النَّاسِ مَنْ مِلْحُهُ عَلَى رُكعبَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The worst of men is he whose fat is upon his knee"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: applied to him who is quickly angered; and to the perfidious: (Meyd, TA:) the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miloHuhu EalaY rukobatihi","text_ar":"مِلْحُهُ عَلَى رُكْبَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also used as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The smallest thing makes him angry:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and a poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"laA talumohaA A_in~ahaA mino EuSobapK\n                      \n                     \n                        miloHuhaA mawoDuwEapN fawoqa Alr~ukabo"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Blame her not; for she is of a set of people whose fat is placed above the knees:"},{"kind":"text","text":"perhaps meaning, for she is but a woman; as women are generally fat in the part above the knee]: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino nisowapK","text_ar":"مِنْ نِسْوَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino EuSobapK","text_ar":"مِنْ عُصْبَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of women whose object of anxiety,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"care, is fatness"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Meyd, TA:) so that the prov. seems to mean that the worst of men is he who has not such intelligence as bids him to do that which is praiseworthy, but only bids him to do that in which is inconstancy and levity, and an inclining to the dispositions of women, to the love of fatness and fat. (Meyd.) [See other explanations in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mlH","text_ar":"ملح"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lower part"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSol","text_ar":"اَصْل"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the plant"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sil~iyaAnap","text_ar":"صِلِّيَانَة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when it has been cut."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","A","K","TA","L","Meyd"]},{"entry_id":"n16461","headword_ar":"رِكْبَةٌ","root":"rkb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of riding."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa Hasanu Alr~ikobapi","text_ar":"هُوَ حَسَنُ الرِّكْبَةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has a good mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of riding."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, * TA.) ―         -b2-  [It is said in the K to be a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakibahu","text_ar":"رَكِبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as though signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A riding."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n16462","headword_ar":"رَكَبَةٌ","root":"rkb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A company of riders upon camels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of owners of camels on a journey,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"travellers upon camels,"},{"kind":"text","text":"exclusively of other beasts, (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but less in number than the company called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakobN","text_ar":"رَكْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) [and probably also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a company of riders upon any beasts, but less than what is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakobN","text_ar":"رَكْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] accord. to MF, it is a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAkibN","text_ar":"رَاكِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^urokuwbN","text_ar":"اُرْكُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["K","S"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}